<paragraph blockId="19.[264,1070,1414,1475]" box="[264,421,1449,1475]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
(
<figureCitation box="[273,413,1449,1475]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–40" captionStartId="20.[264,382,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[413,1165,804,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-235@20.[404,1182,801,1829]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 38–40. Chrysotimus sanjiangyuanus sp. nov. (male). 38. Wing; 39. first flagellomere, lateral view; 40. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048679/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs. 38–40</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[264,1324,1510,1896]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis. Six dc, 3–4 irregularly paired acr. Hairs and bristles on thorax and abdomen brown. Hind tarsomere 1 with group of 5 sparse erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/4 and row of 7–8 pv.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[264,1324,1510,1896]" box="[312,1172,1630,1656]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[463,533,1630,1656]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 2.0– 
<quantity box="[744,851,1630,1656]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="2.05">2.05 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[1009,1168,1630,1656]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.275" metricValueMax="2.35" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="2.275" valueMax="2.35" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.35 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[264,1324,1510,1896]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Head metallic green with pale gray pollen; frons and face brilliant. Hairs and bristles on head brown. Ocellar tubercle weak, with 2 very long oc and 2 very short posterior hairs. Lower postocular bristles (including ventral hairs) pale. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1142,1750,1776]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–40" captionStartId="20.[264,382,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[413,1165,804,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-235@20.[404,1182,801,1829]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 38–40. Chrysotimus sanjiangyuanus sp. nov. (male). 38. Wing; 39. first flagellomere, lateral view; 40. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048679/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
) blackish; first flagellomere blackish, about 0.7 times as long as wide; arista dorsal, with basal segment very short. Proboscis blackish, with brown hairs; palpus dark brown, with 2 brown apical bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[264,1323,284,750]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Thorax metallic green with pale gray pollen, mesonotum and scutellum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on thorax brown; 6 strong dc, 3–4 irregularly paired acr short and hair­like; scutellum with 2 pairs of bristles. Propleuron with 1 blackish bristle on lower portion. Legs including coxae yellow, with all tarsomere 5 brown. Hairs and bristles on legs brownish; fore and mid coxae with yellow hairs and bristles; fore coxa with 2–3 anterior and apical bristles, mid coxa with 3–4 anterior bristles, hind coxa with 1 brown outer bristle near middle. Mid femur with 1 av and 1 short pv apically; hind femur with 1 av and 1 pv apically. Mid tibia with 2 ad and 1 pd, apically with 4 bristles; hind tibia with 1 ad at basal 1/3 and 2–3 pd, apically with 4 bristles. Hind tarsomere 1 with 5 sparse erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/4, and row of 7–8 pv. Relative lengths of tibia and 5 tarsomeres of legs. LI 3.4: 1.8: 0.8: 0.6: 0.4: 0.4; LII 4.3: 2.5: 1.1: 0.9: 0.4: 0.4; LIII 5.0: 2.0: 1.5: 1.0: 0.6: 0.5.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048679" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5048679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048679/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" startId="20.[264,382,1845,1869]" targetBox="[413,1165,804,1824]" targetPageId="20">
<paragraph blockId="20.[264,1322,1845,1903]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,464,1845,1869]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">FIGURES 38–40.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2005" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2005" box="[473,784,1846,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanjiangyuanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[473,784,1846,1869]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Chrysotimus sanjiangyuanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[793,878,1845,1868]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 38. Wing; 39. first flagellomere, lateral view; 40. genitalia, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1325,284,1035]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Wing hyaline (
<figureCitation box="[484,570,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–40" captionStartId="20.[264,382,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[413,1165,804,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-235@20.[404,1182,801,1829]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 38–40. Chrysotimus sanjiangyuanus sp. nov. (male). 38. Wing; 39. first flagellomere, lateral view; 40. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048679/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
), veins brownish; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[803,839,295,316]" fontSize="9" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">4+5</subScript>
and M parallel apically, CuAx ratio 0.25. Squama yellow with pale yellow hairs. Halter brownish with yellow knob.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1325,284,1035]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Abdomen metallic green with pale gray pollen, dorsum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on abdomen brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1325,284,1035]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[497,586,449,475]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–40" captionStartId="20.[264,382,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[413,1165,804,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-235@20.[404,1182,801,1829]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 38–40. Chrysotimus sanjiangyuanus sp. nov. (male). 38. Wing; 39. first flagellomere, lateral view; 40. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048679/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). Epandrium about as long as wide, somewhat square, apically with broad lateral process, and with long and slender process at middle; surstylus long and broad, furcated apically; cercus long, with broad base and long apex, apically with long and strong bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1325,284,1035]" box="[312,536,609,635]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
