</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1325,284,1035]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Comments. This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang and Saigusa" authorityName="Yang and Saigusa" box="[803,1323,809,835]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunlonganus">
<emphasis box="[803,1108,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Chrysotimus yunlonganus</emphasis>
Yang and Saigusa
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[328,421,849,875]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, but may be separated from the latter by hind tarsomere 1 with 5 sparse erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/4 and row of 7–8 pv, and furcated surstylus. In 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunlonganus">
<emphasis box="[1296,1315,889,914]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[264,414,929,954]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">yunlonganus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the hind tarsomere 1 has 8 short black ventral bristles on basal 1/4, and no row of pv; and the surstylus is not furcated apically (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T." box="[879,1182,969,995]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="165 - 188" refId="ref12058" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T. (2001 b) New and little known species of Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from China (IX). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 71, 165 - 188." type="journal article" year="2001">Yang and Saigusa, 2001b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
